author: Felicia Schwartz
title: U.S. Says It Has Met Nuke Reduction Target Under Treaty With Russia
text:
WASHINGTONâ€”The U.S. has met the limits on the number of deployed nuclear warheads it is allowed under a 2010 treaty with Russia, the State Department said, adding that it expects to find Moscow in compliance with its obligations as well.
The State Department on Monday said the U.S. has fulfilled its commitments under the New Strategic Arms Reduction Treaty, or New START, which was signed by former President Barack Obama in 2010 and ratified by the Senate in 2011.
